# Phase 7: Search & Rich Filtering

Adds a powerful, faceted course search and filtering system. Since this project runs locally without an Elasticsearch or Redis cluster, Phase 7 uses **Django ORM full-text search** (`SearchVector` / `SearchQuery` — built into PostgreSQL) with **SQLite fallback via `Q` objects**, combined with **`django-filter`** (already installed) for faceted filtering. This gives a production-grade API without requiring external services.

---

## Approach

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **No Elasticsearch required**: The `elasticsearch` package is in `requirements.txt` but no ES host is configured in `.env`. We will use Django's built-in `SearchVector`/`SearchQuery` with a **`LIKE`-based fallback** that works on both SQLite (dev) and PostgreSQL (prod). This keeps local development fully self-contained.

> [!NOTE]
> A dedicated `GET /api/search/courses/` endpoint is created (separate from the existing `/api/courses/` CRUD list) so the search path is clean and doesn't interfere with role-based CRUD queries. This also makes it easy to point a search bar at it from anywhere in the UI.

