## Proposed Changes

### Backend

#### [NEW] `backend/courses/filters.py`
- `CourseFilter` using `django-filter`:
  - `search` — full-text keyword match on `title`, `description`, and `mentor__username`
  - `level` — exact match (`BEGINNER` / `INTERMEDIATE` / `ADVANCED`)
  - `language` — case-insensitive contains
  - `min_price`, `max_price` — numeric range
  - `min_rating` — aggregate filter (annotate avg rating ≥ value)
  - `ordering` — sort by `price`, `-price`, `created_at`, `-created_at`, `rating`
  - `is_free` — boolean shortcut (`price=0`)

#### [MODIFY] `backend/courses/views.py`
- Add a new `CourseSearchView` (`ListAPIView`):
  - `permission_classes = [AllowAny]` — public search, no login required
  - Queryset: only `is_approved=True, is_published=True` courses
  - Annotates with `avg_rating` (via `Avg('reviews__rating')`) and `enrollment_count` (via `Count('enrollments')`)
  - Applies `CourseFilter` for faceted filtering
  - Returns paginated results (`PageNumberPagination`, `page_size=12`)
  - Returns a `facets` object alongside results containing unique `levels`, `languages`, and `price_range` for the frontend to build dynamic filter panels

#### [MODIFY] `backend/courses/urls.py`
- Add `path('search/', CourseSearchView.as_view(), name='course-search')`

#### [NEW] `backend/courses/serializers.py` *(extend)*
- Add `CourseSearchSerializer` with `avg_rating`, `enrollment_count`, `mentor_name` (read-only)

